<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="357" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[166,794,503,937]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,287,503,527]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body (in alcohol) with brown speckled pigmentation on head, coxae, pleon and urosome. Pereon segment 1 with a forward produced sternal process. Gnathopod 1 basis 2× as long as broad, posterior margin with a distinct knob-like process. Gnathopod 2 coxa deep, ventral margin rounded, with stridulations and a small group of setae; carpus 1.8× as long as broad anterior and posterior margins parallel, posterodistal margin with two teeth, the outer one longer, separated by a V-shaped incision. Pereopod 3–4 basis 1.5× as long as broad, widest medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[166,794,503,937]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Female gnathopod 1 basis slender; propodus palm oblique. Gnathopod 2 coxa deep; carpus posterior margin produced into a lobe with two robust setae and long slender setae; propodus tapered distally, slightly more than twice length of carpus, palm oblique with two robust setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="357" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[166,793,966,1019]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,274,966,990]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Variation</emphasis>
. In some males, the eyes are smaller and do not completely fill the eye-lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
